name: yarn.app.mapreduce.am.containerlauncher.threadpool-initial-size
description:
The initial size of thread pool to launch containers in the
    app master.

name: dfs.stream-buffer-size
description:
The size of buffer to stream files.
  The size of this buffer should probably be a multiple of hardware
  page size (4096 on Intel x86), and it determines how much data is
  buffered during read and write operations.

name: mapreduce.task.merge.progress.records
description:
The number of records to process during merge before
   sending a progress notification to the MR ApplicationMaster.

name: ipc.[port_number].weighted-cost.lockshared
description:
The weight multiplier to apply to the time spent in the
    processing phase which holds a shared (read) lock.
    This property applies to WeightedTimeCostProvider.

name: dfs.datanode.ec.reconstruction.threads
description:
Number of threads used by the Datanode for background
    reconstruction work.

name: yarn.app.mapreduce.client.max-retries
description:
The number of client retries to the RM/HS before
    throwing exception. This is a layer above the ipc.

name: dfs.namenode.get-blocks.max-qps
description:
The maximum number of getBlocks RPCs data movement utilities can make to
    a NameNode per second. Values less than or equal to 0 disable throttling.
    This affects anything that uses a NameNodeConnector, i.e., the Balancer,
    Mover, and StoragePolicySatisfier.
